Weber Sees ‘Much More Drastic’ Policy Action If Markets Worsen

-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 
2011-09-25T16:22:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-25/weber-sees-much-more-drastic-policy-action-if-markets-worsen.html
Axel Weber, the former president of
the Bundesbank, said he sees “much more drastic policy action”
if financial markets worsen.  “I fear very much that the situation will deteriorate
further before it improves,” Weber said today in  Washington .
“We will see much more drastic action” by policy makers if the
situation in financial markets gets worse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
